<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1059,1369,1508]" pageId="9" pageNumber="890">
The record of this flightless species is of particular zoogeographic interest. It was previously known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[498,542,1399,1420]" pageId="9" pageNumber="890">type</typeStatus>
locality, the Gelibolu peninsula, 
<collectingRegion box="[945,1055,1398,1420]" country="Turkey" name="Canakkale" pageId="9" pageNumber="890">Çanakkale</collectingRegion>
, northwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[297,370,1427,1449]" name="Turkey" pageId="9" pageNumber="890">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[391,549,1427,1449]" pageId="9" pageNumber="890" pagination="1 - 54" refId="ref13742" refString="ASSING V. (2007 b): On the Xantholinini of Turkey and adjacent regions (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Staphylininae). - Zootaxa 1474: 1 - 54." type="journal article" year="2007">ASSING 2007b</bibRefCitation>
). Not only do the specimens listed in 
<tableCitation box="[987,1058,1427,1449]" captionStart="Tab" captionStartId="4.[151,192,206,227]" captionTargetBox="[161,1004,212,425]" captionTargetId="graphics@8.[151,1059,204,426]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Tab. 1: Staphylinidae collected in Samothraki in April, 2019. Species preceded by an asterisk (*) most likely represent island endemics." pageId="9" pageNumber="890">Tab. 1</tableCitation>
represent the first records from 
<collectingCountry box="[482,554,1457,1478]" name="Greece" pageId="9" pageNumber="890">Greece</collectingCountry>
and since the original description, these records also confirm a land connection between Samothraki and Northwest 
<collectingCountry box="[838,915,1486,1508]" name="Turkey" pageId="9" pageNumber="890">Turkey</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
